casebody.data:
MULLEN v. DIRECTOR OF PATUXENT INSTITUTION [App. No. 56,

September Term, 1964.]

Decided November 16, 1964.

Before Henderson, C. J., and Hammond, Prescott, HornEy, Sybert and Oppenheimer, JJ.

Per Curiam.

This application for leave to appeal from an order finding the applicant to be a defective delinquent must be dismissed for failure to comply with Maryland Rule 894 a 2(a). Murel v. Director, 231 Md. 661, and cases cited.

Application denied.
